+### D-C.1 · TC-32 — entity dedupe collapses provenance onto the FIRST document *(ACCEPTED, not a defect to fix)*
+
+`dedup_prepared_by_logical_id` keeps the **first** occurrence, so same-name entities extracted from several
+documents collapse onto one `logical_id` row carrying only the **first** document's `source_id`. Erasing a
+later document therefore leaves the shared entity row in place.
+
+The HITL has ruled this **intentional and accepted** for now and explicitly declined a multi-source-provenance
+model ("do not make it more complex"). Tracked as **TC-32**; annotated in code at
+`dedup_prepared_by_logical_id`. It is recorded here so a future reader does not mistake it for an erasure
+completeness gap. Do not change dedupe behaviour on this basis without a fresh HITL decision.
+
